                            <comment id="12677628" author="vzaliva" created="Sat, 28 Feb 2009 02:32:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678376" author="alangates" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 18:08:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m reviewing this script.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678441" author="alangates" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 20:37:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good, passes unit and checkin tests.  IMO this is large improvement over putting DefaultJobName in the job name.  Any other thoughts from other committers before I commit this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678458" author="pkamath" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 21:37:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for the change&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678484" author="olgan" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 22:19:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 as long as it still allows me to set my own name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also what will happen in the multi-store case?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12678510" author="alangates" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2009 23:28:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you set a name via set job.name &apos;foo&apos; in your script, then it overrides this feature.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The name is chosen from the Pig Latin script file, not the store file, so multi-store case won&apos;t be any different.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679025" author="alangates" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 01:14:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch checked in.  Thanks Vadim for the contribution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
